General treatment of teachers communication skills. Teachers communication skills as purposeful ways of acting.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To help learners acquire the basic knowledge of communicative skills necessary for teachers. To help learners acquire the practical skills of using the techniques of leading a discussion and being assertive.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have completed the course:
1. know which teachers behaviour reflects a student-centred attitude;
2. can give an overview of using communication techniques in social interaction;
3. can describe techniques of active listening and can partially use them;
4. can describe techniques of assertiveness and can partially use them;
5. can describe techniques of argumentation and can partially use them.
